# Use Glob Imports, Not Verbose Crate Paths

When using items from other modules, prefer glob imports (`::*`) over verbose `crate::...` paths or itemized imports.

## Anti-patterns

```rust
// Bad: verbose crate path repeated multiple times
crate::vstdplus::seq_set::lemma_seq_index_in_map_to_set(seq, i);
crate::vstdplus::seq_set::lemma_seq_index_in_map_to_set(seq, j);

// Bad: itemized imports duplicate what the module already exports
use crate::Chap19::ArraySeqStPer::ArraySeqStPer::{ArraySeqStPerS, flatten, sum_lens};
```

## Correct Pattern

```rust
// Good: glob import brings all public items into scope
use crate::Chap19::ArraySeqStPer::ArraySeqStPer::*;

flatten(&inner);
let s = ArraySeqStPerS::from_vec(vec);
```

## Why

- Reduces visual noise
- Avoids duplicating what the module already declares as public
- Makes code more readable
- Easier to refactor if module exports change
- The module's `pub` declarations already define the API
